    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan:\n\n## Plan: Add `uv cache stats`\n\n**4 files to touch:**\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to the `CacheCommand` enum and a new `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct (mirrors the existing `SizeArgs`).\n\n2. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new file)* — Implements `cache_stats(cache, human_readable, printer)`. Iterates `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 variants), computes each bucket's size via `diskus::DiskUsage::new(vec![cache.bucket(bucket)]).count_ignoring_errors()`, accumulates a total, and prints `{bucket}: {size}` per line plus `total: {size}` at the end. Non-existent bucket paths yield 0 bytes. Formatting follows the same `human_readable_bytes` pattern as `cache_size.rs`.\n\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;`.\n\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` (no `preview` arg, unlike `cache_size`).",
